# FX Regime Lab — Cursor Rules

## Read First

Always read AGENTS.md before starting any task. Then read TASK.md.

There is **no shipped `web/` frontend** in this repo. Design intent lives in **`claude-design/`**. Prior Supabase read patterns: **`docs/DATA_READS_SPEC.md`**.

## Hard Rules — Python

- All Supabase writes through `pipeline/src/db/writer.py` only
- All AI calls through `pipeline/src/ai/client.py` only
- mypy strict on all pipeline code
- Ruff lint on all pipeline code

## File Location Map

| Need to... | Go to... |
|------------|----------|
| Add a fetcher | `pipeline/src/fetchers/` |
| Add a signal | `pipeline/src/signals/` |
| Change regime logic | `pipeline/src/regime/` |
| Change AI prompts | `pipeline/src/ai/client.py` |
| Write to DB | `pipeline/src/db/writer.py` |
| Understand target UX | `claude-design/` |

## Design Reference

`claude-design/` files are read-only reference. Never import from them into production code until a new app exists.

## Never Do

- Never call AI providers from a future frontend except via explicit product design (today: pipeline only)
- Never bypass `pipeline/src/db/writer.py` for Supabase writes
